description:
With all the ways music affects your body, you can probably already clearly see how music can be used as an effective relaxation and stress management tool. In addition to the many physical changes that music can bring, music is especially helpful in relaxation and stress management because it can be used in the following ways:

Music can promote relaxation of tense muscles, enabling you to easily release some of the tension you carry from a stressful day (or week).

Music can help your brain get into a meditative state, which carries wonderful stress relief benefits with it. For those who find meditation intimidating, music can be an easier alternative.

Music, especially upbeat tunes, can take your mind off what stresses you, and help you feel more optimistic and positive. This helps release stress and can even help you keep from getting as stressed over life's little frustrations in the future.

From silly to science, Emmy Award winner Alan Teitel and his UltraSlo Studio create compelling slow motion video images for online entertainment and education. Slow motion videos from the Ultraslo stock video library are used in documentaries commercials and scientific research world wide. Slow motion videos from UltraSlo have been viewed oner a quarter of a billion times on all the sites that love to stream  slow motion videos around the world

Alan has a unique outlook and viewing perspective based on his twenty-five years of slow motion and 3d work which allow him to see the world at a much different speed. Alan is a director, cinematographer and producer of national commercials, documentaries, and dramatic scenes. 

Alan won two Emmy's for Cinematography and Technical Achievement. Alan has been nominated six times for his outstanding work on broadcast television

David Ferrer (tactics, footwork & fitness)

description:
LatinSoul Productions began in 2007 after Cristina Perez's Nickname as a dancer, LatinSoul. At first, LatinSoul Productions were Hip Hop and Flamenco dance videos but as Perez pursued an education in Television, Film, & New Media Production earning her B.S Degree from SDSU in 2010, LatinSoul Productions grew into a short film and Reality TV style Production company. Cristina's favorite quote is "When you visualize, then you materialize. If you've been there in the mind you'll go there in the body" by: Dr Denis Waitley. 

"My job is to imagine then create the picture as accurately as it was in my mind for you on film, Once I can relive that moment by watching it, I know we are moving forward!" -Cristina Perez

description:
Welcome to the official Youtube channel of Conservation Media®  

We are a digital storytelling studio founded in 2009, and run by and for conservation professionals.

You know that conservation is not just about the science.  It’s also about people, it’s about place, and it’s about a way of life and a shared vision that brings us together.  And most importantly, it’s about story.  Through stunning cinematography, moving interviews, and well-crafted narratives, Conservation Media® knows how to develop a sense of place, strong characters, and show your conservation science in action.

Visit http://www.conservationmedia.com to see exactly what we do and how we do. You can also find us on Instagram, Vimeo, Youtube, Flickr, and Facebook.

description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

description:
To provide quality slow motion videos of baseball pitchers, hitters mechanics and use them as teaching tools when working with students!
Our eyes only see 30 frames per second so when you look at something at full speed, we can only guess what is really going on. When we look at it in slow motion, you are able to see exactly what is going on. Thus, improving teaching quality. I teach hitting and pitching mechanics and use my video library to inspire my students. Please use this library for the same purpose and spread the word!

description:
As the world's largest production house and tourism content archive of factual 4K UHD video from South Asia, you can make us part of your production plans in India/South Asia. We deliver the widest range of production, gear, location, support services and stock footage.

We can open doors that no one else can - creative, aesthetic, bureaucratic and most importantly - those in the mind! And yes, while some of us have a weakness for wildlife, wilderness and the outdoors, we do produce programming on just about every subject under the sun.

The largest global collection of HD internet and television content on South Asia is now online, as a part of Wilderness Films India's 'A Visual mapping of the Indian Subcontinent' initiative which has taken a team of 100 people some 37 years to put together, and we're doubling up our efforts going forward, in order to archive in HD and 4K every aspect of the South Asian experience! We have 125K clips & films and plan to attain 1 million in 2024.

description:
Welcome to our Tarpon and Snook Fishing YouTube channel, where we immerse you in the thrilling world of targeting these legendary gamefish! Join us as we embark on exciting angling adventures in pursuit of the mighty Tarpon and elusive Snook.

Discover the secrets of locating these prized species, unlocking their behavior patterns, and mastering the art of presenting the perfect bait or lure. We'll take you to the most productive hotspots, whether it's stalking the crystal-clear flats, battling the strong currents of inlets, or exploring hidden backwaters.

Whether you're a seasoned angler or just starting your fishing journey, our channel offers something for everyone.

description:
Shane Cole moved to Los Angeles from Jamestown NY in Nov. 1999. He has directed numerous micro-budget horror-thrillers through his company Masked Films, and with his brother under CRC Digital Entertainment - all of which have received general world-wide distribution. He has also directed several music video's and promo trailers for various projects. He learned filmmaking the old-fashioned way, from the ground up, starting out working for free on a few low-budget movies. Soon, however, he was being paid for his production work at TV commercials producer Acme Film Works and later Hyperion Pictures, where he worked on films and TV projects for Disney, HBO, Warner Bros., and many others. He has since moved back to the Finger Lakes area of NY and continues to shoot video / film and photography projects.

description:
The Home for Skateboarding - News, Video Parts, Contest Coverage, Culture and More.

Things change. Boards change, shoes change, tricks change, skaters change. Change is the manifestation of time, and time has shown us that skateboarding is here for as long as we—as individuals and as a community—create it into existence. Although much of the world is trying to stunt skateboarding's growth, there are enough rogue individuals out there continuing to make it happen. Whether it be by building ledges at a remote spot just east of downtown LA, constructing mini-ramps in our backyards, or buying buildings and constructing skateparks inside them like ourselves, we continue to grow because our will to skate and our will to survive is just that strong and because the only alternative is to quit and die. But we at the Berrics believe that life was made to live out of, not die out of. There's nothing special about dying. Anyone can do that. Push the future. —Steve Berra & Eric Koston

description:
Riding Master Rene Gasser, creator and producer for "Gala of The Royal Horses" will be bringing his world-renowned equestrian tour to North America beginning February of 2014.
 
Following in the family footsteps of seven generations, Gasser has recreated a show for this tour only previously seen at the famous riding schools in Vienna and Spain.

The Royal Horses of Europe are some of the most celebrated in history, favoured for centuries by royalty, equestrian riders and bullfighters and this performance will celebrate the tradition, athleticism and grace of these revered creatures.

Gala of The Royal Horses will feature a number of performances involving the Andalusian, Friesian, Lipizzaner and Arabian breeds and the event is dedicated to showing off the amazing beauty and maneuvers these horses are capable of including the stunning maneuvers once used on the battlefield now known as "The Airs Above The Ground".

Coming to The United States in 2014!  Don't Miss it!

I am 23 years old and currently studying Engineering Design in the UK. I have been doing things like this for years now and over time have invested in new tools and equipment for use in my videos.

description:
Based in the beautiful island of Puerto Rico, the sea has been a part of our lives since we were young. In 1996 when we were just 10 & 7 yrs old, our parents took us and our two siblings on the adventure of a life time. We lived on a sailboat for a year sailing all the Lesser Antilles in the Caribbean. Literally living at sea, we took up various hobbies to entertain ourselves and it was then that we learned the amazing things one can do with a simple rope. 
Through the years, rope decorations & knots have always been present in our home, with our father being the master at rope works, we would have plant hangers, mobile sculptures, fruit hangers, jewelry, you name it, all made out of rope. When our sister adopted Gaia, a stray puertorrican lab, we started making rope collars and leashes for her. MODArmory (Cage Code 5XW14) is a government contractor specializing in night vision, thermal and related accessories. Our company only provides the best equipment in the industry. We are located in Colorado Springs, CO and work closely with our Military and Law Enforcement agencies to provide in-depth understanding and rigorous testing of the products we stock. For Law Enforcement we conduct training from basic course work to complete operator's courses. 

Many of the videos featured are from night vision demonstrations, night vision training and other events MOD Armory participates in. All night vision videos are filmed through actual night vision devices and captured with an iPhone. We strive to show you the diverse range of night vision and to give you a basic understanding of what night vision looks like in real world conditions.

description:
Big & Rich is an American country music duo composed of Big Kenny and John Rich, both of whom are songwriters, vocalists, and guitarists. Before the duo's foundation, Rich was bass guitarist in the country band Lonestar, while Kenny was a solo artist for Hollywood Records.

Their first studio album, Horse of a Different Color, was released in 2004. This album produced four straight Top 40 country hits, including the number 11 "Save a Horse (Ride a Cowboy)", plus collaborations with Cowboy Troy, Gretchen Wilson, and Martina McBride. Comin' to Your City was released in November 2005 followed by another Top 20 single the Vietnam War-inspired "8th of November", and two more Top 40 hits. Joining the duo on this album were Cowboy Troy, Wilson, and Kris Kristofferson. Between Raising Hell and Amazing Grace, released in 2007, produced their only No. 1 single, "Lost in This Moment". Both before and during the duo's hiatus, Rich has worked as a producer and songwriter for several other artists.

After this album, both members went on hiatus and released solo albums in 2009—Big Kenny's The Quiet Times of a Rock and Roll Farm Boy and Rich's Son of a Preacher Man. These also produced the duo's first Top 40 solo entries—Big Kenny with "Long After I'm Gone" and Rich with "Shuttin' Detroit Down". In 2010, Big Kenny released his second solo country album, Big Kenny's Love Everybody Traveling Musical Medicine Show Mix Tape, Vol. 1 and in 2011, Rich released the extended plays For the Kids and Rich Rocks, the latter of which included the Top 40 country single "Country Done Come to Town". Big & Rich reunited in May 2011 to release "Fake ID", a cut from the soundtrack to the 2011 film Footloose. A year later, the duo released their fourth album, Hillbilly Jedi, which produced the Top 20 hit "That's Why I Pray. In July 2013, Rich announced that the duo had begun work on their fifth studio album, Gravity, which was released independently.[2][3] Another independent album, Did it For the Party, was announced in 2017 for release in September, led by the single "California."[4] For 2018 "Brand New Buzz" was released as new single go to www.bigandrich.com

description:
The Purple Martin Conservation Association is the largest conservation organization devoted to Purple Martins, with over thirty years leading research projects that study and protect the species. 

This channel was created to share our knowledge and love of these unique birds. Travel with us through the Amazon, learn how to find a migratory roost using weather radar, and much more! We work with state-of-the-art research using geolocator and GPS data-loggers to collect invaluable information on migratory pathways. Our biologists also design and test products that allow people to become successful landlords that you can purchase from the PMCA Shop!

There are many exciting things happening at the PMCA and many ways to get involved. We invite you to join our community! Together we can work to "ensure the future of Purple Martins."

The Purple Martin Conservation Association is a 501(c)(3) tax-exempt charitable organization headquartered in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania (USA).

description:
Hier findet Ihr Videos über mich und Ki-Karate. Ki-Karate ist eine Schulungsmethode. Es werden Ki-Übungen in das Training mit eingebunden und haben ihren festen Platz als einer der Hauptbausteine des Trainings. Ki-Übungen und die Weitergabe und das Nutzen von Wissen über physiologische Vorgänge runden hierbei das Karate Training ab.   
Die Ki-Übungen habe ich bei Meister Aoki aus Spanien gelernt. Außerdem lasse ich aus verschiedenen Bereichen, die sich mit Ki-Arbeit auseinandersetzten, Übungen und Konzepte die mir sinnvoll erscheinen, mit in das Training einfließen. Mein Hauptaugenmerk liegt in der Bewegungs- und Aufmerksamkeitsschulung, Nervensystems-Regulationsübungen und Meditation.

description:
The popular YouTube channel Quint BUILDs originally made in-depth engineering videos on something called GD&T.  It's a standard published by ASME (American Society of Mechanical Engineers) used to define fits of manufactured parts.  Quint has a senior level certification in GD&T and originally made videos to help others understand it.  They're all here FREE for anyone looking for help on that topic.  You may still see new content here but most of Quint's effort is currently directed to Quint BUILDs.  That content is more appealing to a general audience which is why it gets MILLIONS of views rather than thousands.  
 
If you gained something from these videos and want to give back, you can make a one time contribution on PayPal:  qcrispin@gmail.com  or consider becoming a patron of Quint BUILDs.  

There's also one piece of pay-only content, a study guide Quint created based on the free videos.
Find more on that here:  https://youtu.be/WLQJ8q_zpA0

Thanks and good luck learning GD&T!

Photo Booth Solutions creates unique software for the photo booth and event photography industry with a focus on interactivity and social media.
Social Booth - A full featured photo booth software featuring both DSLR and Webcam support, Filters and Social Media uploads, right at the booth.
Photo Booth Connected - Set up Social Media Upload stations to allow users to share their photos live at your event. 
BYO Booth - Set up Instagram & Twitter Print Stations and Slideshows. Crowd source your event photos by allowing users to take photos with their smart phones and instantly print and display them in real time.
Sketch Booth - The most interactive photo booth software on the market. Draw on the screen and drag and drop virtual props and stickers. Set up your own DIY version of Photo Mingle or Tap Snap.
Guest Booth - Let guests leave photo or video messages and actually sign right on the screen. Give your hosts a digital guestbook to browse and enjoy.
